removed.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
removed.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

removed.title: Los Acantilados de la Histeria
removed.description: Los Ninjas suben a los Acantilados de la histeria y descubren que Unagami convierte a los jugadores en cubos de energía para construir un portal.

removed.title: Polos Opuestos
removed.description: Un viaje al Polo Sur queda patas arriba cuando el equipo Tennyson aterriza en el Polo Norte. Pero Ben rápidamente descubre a los culpables: iSolar y Polar Twain, unos científicos con poder magnético que quieren chantajear al mundo amenazando con invertir los polos magnéticos de la Tierra!

removed.title: Last Laugh
removed.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

removed.title: Kevin 11
removed.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

removed.title: Tourist Trap
removed.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

removed.title: Hunted
removed.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

removed.title: The Alliance
removed.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

removed.title: Sidekicked to the Curb
removed.description: When Bam is sent to take on Prank, Redbird is forced to hang back because The Joker's van is too dangerous! When Bam discovers that Redbird secretly tagged along, he's upset… until Redbird bails him out of a tight spot.

removed.title: Some Assembly Required
removed.description: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

removed.title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song - Healthy Habits!
removed.description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

removed.title: Bee a Bee dance
removed.description: Come sing this song and dance with our Lellobee City Farm friends to learn how to move like a Bee! Ella, Izzy, and Lettie are having fun playing and learning about bees!

removed.title: What's in a Name?
removed.description: When Cranky gets overwhelmed on a busy and blustery day at Brendam Docks, he accidentally gets Riff and Jiff's names confused, sending them on opposite deliveries. An observant Thomas hears the mistake, but does not correct the crankier-than-usual crane -- thinking, grown-ups don't make mistakes! Thomas is proven wrong, however, when he ends up at Whiff's Recycling Plant and old tires are delivered to McColl's Farm because of Cranky's error. After calming the chaos in both places, Thomas learns that it is important to speak up and tell someone they are making a mistake --- even if it is a grown-up!
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Keep Calm and Roll On
removed.description: After Jestah's insults get the best of her, a short-tempered Bibi tries to not let the big-wheeled bully's words get to her so she can help Batgirl catch Harley.

removed.title: Ocean
removed.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

removed.title: The Growing Song
removed.description: Let's celebrate everything that grows with the Growing Song! Come sing along! Have you ever noticed that everything is changing? Watch the different seasons of the year and revisit plants, animals, children, and buildings in the farm and city to see how they've grown.

removed.title: Mystery Boxcars
removed.description: Kana is upset when she keeps running out of power, but a mystery scavenger hunt is just the thing to cheer her up.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: The Sandman Is Coming
removed.description: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes.

removed.title: Bring it On Beresford
removed.description: On Plant-A-Tree Day on Sodor, Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the most impressive pine for the holiday, but they'll have to compete by delivering all the other trees first. When Thomas wins the race and the pine is loaded onto his flatcar, he discovers that he overestimated the job and himself, resulting in the tree falling in a deep ditch! Luckily, Beresford the Crane has a plan to aid the Number One Engine! Will they be able to plant the biggest tree before the end of the holiday?
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Tea & Basketball
removed.description: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys.

removed.title: Did Not! Did Too!
removed.description: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

removed.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
removed.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

removed.title: Mountain
removed.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

removed.title: Snow Cap
removed.description: Pauleen Penguin hires The Looney Builders to build her a home in Looneyburg. Lola soon discovers they got the design wrong and the crew has to make adjustments.

removed.title: Gravity
removed.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

removed.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
removed.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

removed.title: Planets
removed.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

removed.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
removed.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

removed.title: Honey
removed.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

removed.title: Tweety-Go-Round
removed.description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

removed.title: Overnight Stop
removed.description: Percy feels anxious about spending a night away from home during an overnight delivery with Thomas and Nia.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Super Screen Cleaners
removed.description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Wheels on the Bus
removed.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

removed.title: All Washed Up
removed.description: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath.

removed.title: Welcome to Zombozo-Zone!
removed.description: During medieval times, Team Tennyson must fight to remember that they're not in the past at all, but actually at a Renaissance-esque faire, where "King Zombozo" has hypnotized its guests into thinking they live in the past!

removed.title: Show Don't Tell
removed.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

removed.title: Poles Apart
removed.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

removed.title: Rath of Con
removed.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.
